Rendezvous (Noun)
[rawn-day-voo]
It's a French term that is being used in English language now.

Meanings-  
1. Meeting that you have arranged with somebody.
2. A place where people often meet.

Example- If you want to improve your spoken English, you can watch the famous show 'Rendezvous (meeting) with Simi Grewal'.

Cafeteria is a popular rendezvous (place) for the students.

Pronunciation - https://dictionary.cambridge.org/pronunciation/english/rendezvous
